  #information
    %h3 Information that We Collect and Store
    %p We only collect, store or use information that we consider necessary for the purpose of providing the best service possible to all of our members. You are free to browse our Website [and Apps] without providing any personal information to us however you will need to provide some personal information for the purpose of logging in to your account and/or rating, reviewing or commenting on a supplier who advertises through the Service ("Supplier").

    %p Users who wish to rate, review or provide comment on a Supplier must register and provide us with their name, contact details and a secure password. We ask Suppliers for further information including their company logo and payment details. We store this information on our secure server.

    %p The vast majority of the material on the Website [and our Apps] originates from our users, and we rely on them to accurately rate, review or provide comment on Suppliers. We also hold any information that the user has provided as part of the sign-up process in relation to his or her wedding, such as the location and date.

    %p For quality control and training purposes, we may monitor or record your communication with our support team.

    = link_to 'back to top', '#top', class: 'top_link'

  #how_we_use
    %h3 How We Use this Information
    %p We check the accuracy of the information that you provide on registration and during your continued use of the Service and remind you of your obligations to provide accurate information to us as set out in our respective User Agreements.

    %p We may use the contact information you provide to contact you via email, fax, post or telephone regarding your registration, or any other matter that we consider relevant to your use of our Service.

    %p We may contact you by email for the purpose of sending our own marketing communications or marketing communications sent by an associated third party marketing partner. You have the right to opt-out of such communications via our user consent mechanisms.

    %p We may use any information we collect about you, including any information we may have obtained from your use of the Service, to resolve disputes, provide customer support, troubleshoot problems and enforce our User Agreements and policies. We may look across multiple users to identify problems or resolve disputes. In the unlikely event that fees remain unpaid on the account of a Supplier, we may pass your business information to a credit recovery company.

    %p We may disclose your personal information if we are compelled to do so by law, or in response to a valid, legally compliant request by a law enforcement or governmental authority. We may also disclose aggregated demographic and profile data (in which neither you nor any other individual is identified) to our commercial and marketing partners.

    = link_to 'back to top', '#top', class: 'top_link'


  #security
    %h3 Security Measures

    %p To prevent unauthorised access, maintain accuracy of our records and to ensure proper use and protection of your information, we have put appropriate physical, electronic and managerial procedures in place. However, we cannot guarantee the security of any information or data which is transmitted over public or third party networks. Please note: you must ensure that your password remains secret.

    = link_to 'back to top', '#top', class: 'top_link'

